{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"slug":1,"metadata":2,"inscription":41,"license":71,"title":42},"ISic003291",{"file":1,"metadataFile":3,"htmlFile":4,"uri":5,"title":6,"status":7,"type":8,"notBefore":12,"notAfter":13,"geo":14,"facsimile":17,"country":20,"region":21,"settlement":22,"textLang":23,"place":26,"placeName":27,"keywords":30},"metadata/ISic003291.json","html/ISic003291.json","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic003291","Epitaph of Rouphina and Hesychios","draft",{"_":9,"ana":10,"ref":11},"funerary","#function.funerary","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html",301,500,[15,16],37,15,{"url":18,"desc":19},"ISic003291_tiled.tif","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana","Italy","Sicily","Catania",{"_":24,"mainLang":25},"Ancient Greek","grc",{"_":27,"type":28,"ref":29},"Catina","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462270",[31,32,7,33,34,35,36,37,38,36,39,40,25],"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/isic003291","epitaph of rouphina and hesychios","301","500","catina","catania","italy","sicily","museo civico di catania","ancient greek",{"title":42,"body":43,"divs":44,"images":65},"ISic003291. Epitaph of Rouphina and Hesychios","  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003291_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003291_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic003291.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic003291-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"edition\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">------\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al1\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> μητ]έρα μου ⸢Ῥ⸣ουφῖνα̣[ν \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] Ἡσύχιος ((·)) ζήσα[ς \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> ἠγορ]ήσατο αὐτο[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] πάντα τ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]υτα οὖν Σ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΓΙΑ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cp>  \u003Cspan class=\"\">\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">\u003Cspan>lapis: ΙΟΥΦΙΝ; Korhonen: ουφῖν[αν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: ζήσα[ς]; Pleket: ζήσα[σαν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [ἠγορ]ήσατο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Σ, but it could also be a Ο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Γ, but it could also be a T\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>…my mother Rouphinan … Hesychios, while alive, purchased … all …\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>… mia madre Rouphinan … Hesychios, mentre era vivo, acquistò … tutto …\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph must have been partly metrical (ll. 1-2), as Korhonen pointed out. It can be assumed that Hesychios had acquired the burial place while alive (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζήσας\u003C/span>) for his mother Rouphina (for himself and another deceased (?): \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αὐτοῖς\u003C/span>). At l. 4 a supplement could be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν χρόνον\u003C/span> to indicate the permanent possession of the purchase of the tomb or with \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν τόπον\u003C/span> to indicate the purchase of the entire place for the burial of the deceased. The names Rouphina and Hesychios recur in Christian epitaphs from Syracuse, see SEG 36.872 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002932\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002932\u003C/a>, IG 14.164 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000985\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000985\u003C/a>, Agnello 1950: 60 no.11 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002918\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002918\u003C/a>. \u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 2004.0655 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 54.0910 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 194 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[45,48,51,54,56,59,62],{"id":46,"html":47},"edition","  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\">  \u003Ca id=\"al0\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">------\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al1\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> μητ]έρα μου ⸢Ῥ⸣ουφῖνα̣[ν \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al2\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] Ἡσύχιος ((·)) ζήσα[ς \u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al3\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span> ἠγορ]ήσατο αὐτο[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al4\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] πάντα τ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al5\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]υτα οὖν Σ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003Cbr id=\"al6\">[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΓΙΑ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  ",{"id":49,"html":50},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cp>  \u003Cspan class=\"\">\u003Cspan>Text based on photograph\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003Cspan class=\"line 1\">\u003Cspan>lapis: ΙΟΥΦΙΝ; Korhonen: ουφῖν[αν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 2\">line.2: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: ζήσα[ς]; Pleket: ζήσα[σαν]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 3\">line.3: \u003Cspan>Korhonen: [ἠγορ]ήσατο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Σ, but it could also be a Ο\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>  \u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Korhonen reads a Γ, but it could also be a T\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003C/p>",{"id":52,"html":53},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>…my mother Rouphinan … Hesychios, while alive, purchased … all …\u003C/p>  ",{"id":52,"html":55},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>… mia madre Rouphinan … Hesychios, mentre era vivo, acquistò … tutto …\u003C/p>  ",{"id":57,"html":58},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph must have been partly metrical (ll. 1-2), as Korhonen pointed out. It can be assumed that Hesychios had acquired the burial place while alive (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζήσας\u003C/span>) for his mother Rouphina (for himself and another deceased (?): \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αὐτοῖς\u003C/span>). At l. 4 a supplement could be \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν χρόνον\u003C/span> to indicate the permanent possession of the purchase of the tomb or with \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">[πάντα τ]ὸν τόπον\u003C/span> to indicate the purchase of the entire place for the burial of the deceased. The names Rouphina and Hesychios recur in Christian epitaphs from Syracuse, see SEG 36.872 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002932\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002932\u003C/a>, IG 14.164 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000985\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000985\u003C/a>, Agnello 1950: 60 no.11 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic002918\" target=\"_blank\">ISic002918\u003C/a>. \u003C/p>  ",{"id":60,"html":61},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>  \u003Cli> 2004.0655 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001283\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 54.0910 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>  \u003Cli> 194 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscripti